 as a focus of social interaction between adversaries, and as a means of projecting imperial power. It will make fascinating reading for students, academics and enthusiasts in military and imperial history, Victorian studies, railway history and colonial warfare.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMilitary railroadszEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 4aStudies in Imperialism 2017. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aBritish army.  aCrimean War.  aEgypt.  aFirst World War.  aSouth Africa.  aSudan Military Railway.  aVictorian army.  aactive service.  acivil power.  acolonial operations.  adomestic emergencies.  aforeign wars.  ahome defence.  alogistic planning.  amilitary success.  aoperational management.  arailway age.  astrategic defence.  astrategic planning.1 aSpiers, Edward M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499180740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784991807423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784991807/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles